records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jordan M. Guynes in court with attorney Gary Stephen Dodge.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Court calls  @ 9:089 am.  State gives plea agreement, ct 1 plea, ct 2 dismissed & consolidated, withheld sentence 1 year probation, AODA & follow through, counseling & costs.  No victim rights. Atty Dodge would like to be heard on expungement & State objects to expungement.  Def. agrees with plea agreement.  Plea questionnaire, & waiver rights filed.  Court reviews plea questionnaire. Ct 1 Guilty, Ct 2 Dismissed. Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. Rights. Def. advised of elements. Atty Dodge is satisfied. Court finds plea is freely & voluntarily given, accepts plea.  Parties stipulate to Factual basis in complaint, Court finds factual basis from complaint & finds def. Guilty to ct 1.  State gives sentencing argument. Atty Dodge gives sentencing argument.  Court question expungement & questions case law.  Atty Dodge will need to complete resource. State replys. Def. has nothing to say.  
Court accepts & orders withheld sentence 1 year probation, AODA & follow through, counseling deemed by agent & costs, No DNA sample or surcharge, not ordering.  Expungement, not granting, Atty Dodge to file resource & will reserve ruling, but denying expungement at this time. Def. advised of postconviction rights.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Defendant Jordan M. Guynes in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint received, reviewed, and waive reading.  Not guilty pleas entered.  Court will accept pleas.  Bond will continue  Status conference scheduled for May 4, 2015 at 03:30 pm
